FT  01 FEB 94 / UK Company News: Healthcare Hldgs
Healthcare Holdings has completed the sale of two hospitals to General de
Sante International for Pounds 6.5m cash. Proceeds will be used to repay
bank borrowings and other unsecured creditors.
Directors confirmed that the group had entered into non-binding heads of
agreement with a third party with a view to a recommended offer being made
for Healthcare. The shares remain suspended.
